events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Payton Pritchard scored a career-high 43 points and knocked down a career-best 10 3-pointers to lead the short-handed Boston Celtics past the Portland Trail Blazers 128-118 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pritchard scores career-high 43, knocks down 10 3s to lead Celtics over Blazers 128-118

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards and Jaden McDaniels scored 29 points apiece and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Charlotte Hornets 125-110 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards and McDaniels each score 29 points as Wolves send Hornets to eighth straight loss

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 26 points, Darius Garland had 10 assists and the Cleveland Cavaliers survived some sloppiness in the final two minutes to win their 12th straight game, 112-107 over the banged-up Miami Heat on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers hold off Heat 112-107 to extend winning streak to 12 and clinch playoff spot

headlines.description: — Kyshawn George scored 23 points, Alex Sarr added 21 and the Washington Wizards edged the Utah Jazz 125-122 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: George, Sarr help Wizards hand Jazz their 10th straight road loss with 125-122 victory

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 32 points to bring his career total over 20,000, Damian Lillard added 34 points and Kevin Porter Jr. had a triple-double as the surging Milwaukee Bucks trounced the short-handed Dallas Mavericks 137-107 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo joins 20,000-point club as Bucks roll past short-handed Mavericks 137-107

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 22 points and 14 rebounds, Russell Westbrook scored 25 points, and the Denver Nuggets rallied in the fourth quarter to beat the Sacramento Kings 116-110 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has 22 points, 14 rebounds, Nuggets beat Kings, 116-110

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 41 points and keyed a third-quarter rally as the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Memphis Grizzlies 120-103 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 41 points as Thunder beat Grizzlies 120-103

headlines.description: — James Harden scored 50 points, his 24th career 50-point game and first with the Clippers, as Los Angeles beat the Detroit Pistons 123-115...
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden scores 50 points for 1st time with Clippers as Los Angeles beats Pistons 123-115
